        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:35PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Long Creek, or 7 miles southwest of Burgaw, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Torrential rainfall is also
occurring with this storm and may lead to localized
flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rocky Point, Castle Hayne, Long Creek, The Borough, Malpass Corner,
Montague, Currie, and Wrightsboro.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between mile markers 407 and 414.
Interstate 140 between mile markers 16 and 17.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Do not
drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Continuous cloud to
ground lightning is occurring with this storm. Lightning is one of
nature's leading killers.</instruction>
